<div class="ds-eyebrow">Reusable page templates</div>
<h1 class="ds-title">Desktop layouts</h1>
<p class="ds-lede">These eight golden pages <strong>are</strong> the design system's reusable page templates — the place to start a new page. Each is a complete, on-brand layout served byte-identical from the package, and every one ships a matching mobile layout from the same file (see <a href="/responsive/">Responsive layouts</a>). To build a page: pick the archetype closest to what you need, copy its file from <code>package/examples/</code>, keep the chrome, and swap in your content.</p>
<div class="ds-example-grid">
{% set pages = [
  {file: "index.html", name: "Home", desc: "Landing hub — hero banner plus featured sections."},
  {file: "briefs.html", name: "Briefs", desc: "Featured brief plus filterable card grid."},
  {file: "brief-detail.html", name: "Brief detail", desc: "Full article with sticky header and progress bar."},
  {file: "editorial.html", name: "Editorial", desc: "Three-column grid of editorial cards."},
  {file: "editorial-detail.html", name: "Editorial detail", desc: "Hero, methodology, profiles, newsletter form."},
  {file: "podcasts.html", name: "Podcasts", desc: "Horizontal-scroll rails with audio player."},
  {file: "games.html", name: "Games", desc: "Grid of game cards."},
  {file: "newsletter.html", name: "Newsletter", desc: "Split-layout signup form."}
] %}
{% for p in pages %}
  <a class="ds-component-card" href="/examples/pages/{{ p.file }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
    <span class="cat">template</span>
    <h3>{{ p.name }}</h3>
    <p>{{ p.desc }}</p>
    <p class="ds-example-src">copy <code>package/examples/{{ p.file }}</code></p>
  </a>
{% endfor %}
</div>
<style>
  .ds-example-src { margin-top: 10px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-muted, #b3a6c8); }
  .ds-example-src code { font-size: 11.5px; }
</style>
